comments:
Personally I didn't notice anything unusual about the alien words. The strategies that I used to learn them were: For the -pens one, the shape reminded me of a pencil sharpener so I associated it this way. For the -pods one, the picture reminded me of my two circular earpods. For the one containing a lot of i (I cannot recall the word - maybe stymiks?), it was very different from every other word, also the i reminded me of spikes which is what the shape looked like (like a cactus with spikes). 
 In the beginning I found it hard to separate between the first two shapes (on the line) and words, both words looked very similar. It later on became easier and easier. The last part of the study when I had to stare at the cross was much easier in my opinion than the first one, because even though I did not have time to adjust to the word, I could easily make a decision without thinking too much about it and I eventually ended up choosing the right shape.
